1
00:00:04,038 --> 00:00:05,971
I TOLD JAROD HE WAS WELCOME
IN THE CREW QUARTERS,

2
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:09,041
BUT HE SAID
HE WANTED TO BE HERE,
NEARER THE ANIMALS.

3
00:00:09,109 --> 00:00:11,409
CAREFUL WHERE YOU WALK.
HE LET SOME OF THEM RUN FREE.

4
00:00:11,478 --> 00:00:15,814
<i> LET'S SEE IF HE LEFT</i>
<i> ANYTHING ELSE BESIDES...</i>
<i> THIS STENCH.</i>

5
00:00:15,882 --> 00:00:18,450
OH, LOOK AT THESE.
<i> WILD KINGDOM,</i>
<i> NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC.</i>

6
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:20,485
<i>HEY, HERE'S</i>
<i>THAT CROCODILE GUY.</i>

7
00:00:20,554 --> 00:00:23,255
[ Australian Accent ]
"THAT MAMMOTH SNAKE'S
A REAL BEAUTY, AIN'T SHE?

8
00:00:23,323 --> 00:00:25,623
I'M GONNA TRY
AND RIDE HER."

9
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:29,394
<i> YOU WERE SAYING</i>
<i> THAT JAROD CLAIMED TO BE</i>
<i> AN ANIMAL BEHAVIORIST?</i>

10
00:00:29,463 --> 00:00:31,596
YEAH. SOME ZOO UP NORTH.
SOME PLACE IN, UH--

11
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:35,133
<i> BLUE COVE, DELAWARE?</i>
<i> THAT'S WHERE</i>
<i> I'VE BEEN WAITING...</i>

12
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:37,635
SINCE SOMEONE FAILED
TO NOTIFY ME ABOUT
THIS LITTLE ROAD TRIP.

13
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:39,337
LYLE--
<i> IT'S AN OVERSIGHT.</i>

14
00:00:39,406 --> 00:00:42,473
- YOUR PEOPLE WERE GONNA
CALL MY PEOPLE.
- ACTUALLY, I WAS GOING TO SAY--

15
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:46,278
-<i> [ Squishing Sound ]</i>
- WATCH YOUR STEP.

16
00:00:46,347 --> 00:00:51,617
<i> SO, THIS IS ALL JAROD DID?</i>
<i> JUST WATCH TV AND, UH, PLAY</i>
<i> WITH HIS FURRY FRIENDS?</i>

17
00:00:51,685 --> 00:00:55,286
ACTUALLY, HE SPENT
MOST OF HIS TIME IN FRONT
OF THE CHIMPANZEE CAGES.

18
00:00:55,356 --> 00:00:57,422
HE'D SIT THERE FOR HOURS,
MESMERIZED.

19
00:00:57,491 --> 00:00:59,691
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> JAROD KNOWS THE AGONY</i>
<i> OF BEING CAGED.</i>

20
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:03,161
THE PRYING EYES.
THAT'S WHY HE STUDIED
THE CHIMPS,

21
00:01:03,229 --> 00:01:06,030
BECAUSE HE RELATED
TO THEM.
[ Laughs ]

22
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:08,766
NAH. HE JUST LIKED
WATCHING THEM DO IT.

23
00:01:08,835 --> 00:01:12,170
IT?
YEAH, YOU KNOW, MATE.

24
00:01:13,507 --> 00:01:15,607
<i> OKAY, WEIRD TIME.</i>

25
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:19,445
HOT PEPPERMINT-FLAVORED
MASSAGE OIL.

26
00:01:19,513 --> 00:01:23,548
FEATHER TICKLERS.
EDIBLE APPAREL.

27
00:01:23,617 --> 00:01:27,385
I GUESS IT'S ALL
FOR, UH, FOR--

28
00:01:27,454 --> 00:01:30,221
SEX, BROOTS.
THE WORD IS SEX.

29
00:01:32,192 --> 00:01:34,960
LOOKS LIKE
OUR LITTLE MONKEY'S IN HEAT.

30
00:01:36,029 --> 00:01:38,563
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>OH, GOOD MORNING.</i>

31
00:01:38,631 --> 00:01:41,866
<i>YOU MUST BE DR. KINSEY.</i>
<i>WELCOME TO THE ARNETT CENTER.</i>

32
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:45,370
THANK YOU, NURSE PLENTY?

33
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:47,806
- PLEN-TAY.
- AH.

34
00:01:47,874 --> 00:01:49,808
I TOOK THE LIBERTY OF
GETTING YOU ALL SET UP.

35
00:01:49,876 --> 00:01:53,211
YOUR DAILY SCHEDULE IS HERE.
YOUR WEEKLY HERE.

36
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,413
HERE'S A LITTLE PAMPHLET
TO EXPLAIN THE PHONES.

37
00:01:55,482 --> 00:01:59,351
<i> AND SINCE I DIDN'T KNOW</i>
<i> WHICH YOU PREFER, I BROUGHT</i>
<i> YOU TEA AND COFFEE.</i>

38
00:01:59,420 --> 00:02:02,487
WELL, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
THAT'S GREAT.

39
00:02:02,556 --> 00:02:06,858
AT THE ARNETT SEX CENTER,
SATISFACTION IS OUR MOTTO.

40
00:02:08,161 --> 00:02:10,395
WAS THERE SOMETHING ELSE
YOU NEEDED?

41
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:12,664
OH, YES, DOCTOR.

42
00:02:12,732 --> 00:02:16,934
THERE IS SOMETHING
I NEED VERY BADLY.

43
00:02:18,571 --> 00:02:20,838
UH, NURSE PLENTY, I--

44
00:02:20,907 --> 00:02:22,908
PLEN-TAY.
UH--

45
00:02:22,977 --> 00:02:27,111
OH! I AM SO SORRY, DOCTOR.

46
00:02:27,180 --> 00:02:29,747
<i> MONIQUE SLIPPED</i>
<i> RIGHT PAST ME.</i>

47
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:31,783
SHE'S NOT REALLY
A NURSE, IS SHE?

48
00:02:31,852 --> 00:02:36,421
- NO. SHE'S YOUR 9:00 PATIENT.
-<i> AH. MONIQUE BROOKS.</i>

49
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:41,226
SUFFERING FROM
AN UNCONTROLLABLE URGE
FOR SEXUAL ROLE PLAYING.

50
00:02:42,562 --> 00:02:45,430
WE ALL LIKE TO PRETEND
ONCE IN A WHILE, DON'T WE, DOC?

51
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:49,600
UH-HUH.

52
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:52,804
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

53
00:02:52,873 --> 00:02:54,806
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

54
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:58,443
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

55
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:01,913
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

56
00:03:01,982 --> 00:03:05,417
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

57
00:03:05,486 --> 00:03:07,686
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

58
00:03:07,755 --> 00:03:10,522
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

59
00:03:10,591 --> 00:03:13,324
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

60
00:03:13,393 --> 00:03:16,327
<i>- [ Miss Parker ] HE DEFENDS</i>
<i>  THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>
<i>- [ Jarod ] LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

61
00:03:28,108 --> 00:03:30,575
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

62
00:03:38,418 --> 00:03:40,619
<i>IT WENT FROM A COUPLE OF</i>
<i>QUICKIES ON THE DRYER--</i>

63
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:42,621
TO THE UPPER DECK
AT DODGER STADIUM.

64
00:03:42,689 --> 00:03:46,324
WE CRAVE DARING PLACES.
NEED DARING PLACES.

65
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:48,627
<i> IT NEVER OCCURRED TO US</i>
<i> THAT WE HAD A PROBLEM.</i>

66
00:03:48,695 --> 00:03:50,795
UNTIL THIS.

67
00:03:50,864 --> 00:03:54,600
<i>THE PARAMEDICS SAID</i>
<i>WE WERE LUCKY FALLING OFF</i>
<i>THE SCOREBOARD LIKE WE DID.</i>

68
00:03:54,668 --> 00:03:59,070
<i> IF IT WEREN'T</i>
<i> FOR THE PEANUT GUY?</i>
<i> WE MIGHT HAVE BEEN KILLED.</i>

69
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,640
HMM.

70
00:04:02,709 --> 00:04:04,642
WE'VE BEEN TOGETHER
FIVE YEARS.

71
00:04:04,712 --> 00:04:08,180
AND... WE'RE STILL,

72
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,181
YOU KNOW--

73
00:04:11,351 --> 00:04:15,487
UNSPOILED...
AFTER FIVE YEARS.

74
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:20,725
WELL, MANY PEOPLE
CHOOSE TO WAIT.

75
00:04:20,794 --> 00:04:24,629
<i>IN THE GRAND SCHEME OF THINGS,</i>
<i>FIVE YEARS REALLY</i>
<i>ISN'T THAT LONG.</i>

76
00:04:24,698 --> 00:04:27,232
WE'VE BEEN MARRIED
FOR FOUR OF THEM.

77
00:04:28,669 --> 00:04:32,871
WE HAVE SOME VIDEOS HERE
I THINK MIGHT HELP.

78
00:04:34,641 --> 00:04:37,242
THANK YOU VERY MUCH!

79
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:40,312
JUST DON'T TRY EVERYTHING
IN ONE NIGHT.

80
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,480
EXCUSE ME.
YOU MUST BE DR. KINSEY.

81
00:04:42,549 --> 00:04:45,583
THAT'S WHAT IT SAYS
ON MY DOOR ANYWAY.
I'M DR. COVNEY.

82
00:04:45,653 --> 00:04:48,753
ALL MY PATIENTS
CALL ME ALLEN.
NICE TO MEET YOU, ALLEN.

83
00:04:48,821 --> 00:04:51,389
HEY. HOW MANY
SEX THERAPISTS DOES IT TAKE
TO CHANGE A LIGHTBULB?

84
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,758
IS THERE A LIGHTBULB
THAT I CAN HELP YOU CHANGE?

85
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:55,861
IT'S JUST--
IT'S JUST A JOKE.

86
00:04:55,929 --> 00:04:59,697
<i>[ Man ] SORT OF LIKE</i>
<i>THE FUNNY ONES, ONLY DIFFERENT.</i>
<i>GET USED TO IT, JAROD.</i>

87
00:04:59,766 --> 00:05:03,334
SEX THERAPY'S THE BUTT OF A LOT
OF JOKES. THE WORK WE DO AT THIS
CLINIC IS IMPORTANT.

88
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:06,270
SPEAKING OF WHICH,
DR. ARNETT, MY 11:00 GROUP
IS WAITING.

89
00:05:06,339 --> 00:05:08,272
WELCOME ABOARD.
THANK YOU.

90
00:05:08,342 --> 00:05:11,076
JAROD, YOU GOT A MINUTE?
UH, SURE.

91
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:17,215
SYD, DO YOU EVER WONDER
WHY THESE DOLLS...

92
00:05:17,284 --> 00:05:20,918
<i>ALWAYS HAVE THE SAME SURPRISED</i>
<i>EXPRESSION ON THEIR FACE?</i>

93
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:27,359
- [ Snickers ]
- GO AHEAD. SAY IT.

94
00:05:28,929 --> 00:05:30,929
<i>THIS IS FISH IN A BARREL</i>
<i>TERRITORY.</i>

95
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:34,298
TELL ME ABOUT THIS STUFF, BOYS.
LOOKS LIKE JAROD COULD USE
A NICE COLD SHOWER.

96
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:36,902
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>WELL, HIS IS</i>
<i>AN INQUISITIVE MIND.</i>

97
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:41,406
NO REASON HE WOULDN'T USE IT
TO EXPLORE HIS SENSUALITY.

98
00:05:41,475 --> 00:05:43,741
SYD'S FANCY WAY OF SAYING
OUR BOY HAS HIS HORNS UP.

99
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:46,778
[ Chuckles ]
HORNS UP.

100
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:49,314
SO, DID YOU FIND
ANYTHING USEFUL?

101
00:05:49,382 --> 00:05:52,718
UH, WELL, BASICALLY WHATEVER
TURNS YOU ON, BABY.

102
00:05:54,954 --> 00:05:59,424
TO LOCATE JAROD?
STILL LOOKIN'.
MAYBE WE'LL GET LUCKY.

103
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:03,894
- I'LL KEEP YOU POSTED.
- THANK YOU.

104
00:06:03,963 --> 00:06:07,465
<i>[ Lyle ]</i>
<i>FORGET TO CALL ME AGAIN?</i>

105
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:10,334
<i> DON'T WORRY, LYLE.</i>
<i> YOU CAN PLAY WITH THE TOYS</i>
<i> WHEN WE'RE DONE.</i>

106
00:06:10,404 --> 00:06:14,306
<i> THE GAME'S CHANGING.</i>
<i> DUE TO RECENT LAPSES</i>
<i> IN COMMUNICATION,</i>

107
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:18,777
I HAVE DECIDED TO TAKE
A MORE SUPERVISORY ROLE
IN THE HUNT FOR JAROD.

108
00:06:18,845 --> 00:06:23,514
FROM NOW ON,
YOU'LL REPORT EVERY ASPECT
OF YOUR SEARCH TO ME.

109
00:06:23,584 --> 00:06:25,750
<i> EVERY ASPECT.</i>

110
00:06:25,819 --> 00:06:29,954
AND IF WE DON'T,
YOU'LL GO UP TO THE TOWER
AND GET US IN LOTS OF TROUBLE.

111
00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:33,525
TATTLETALE WILL GO
SO NICELY ON YOUR RÉSUMÉ.

112
00:06:34,861 --> 00:06:38,329
LIKE YOU SAID,
WATCH YOUR STEP.

113
00:06:46,039 --> 00:06:49,874
REPORTING TO MR. LYLE
CAN'T BE GOOD.
WONDER WHAT THAT MEANS?

114
00:06:49,942 --> 00:06:52,310
I KNOW WHAT IT MEANS
TO ME. NOTHING.

115
00:06:52,378 --> 00:06:56,214
<i>I DON'T ANSWER TO ANYONE.</i>
<i>ESPECIALLY MY LITTLE BROTHER.</i>

116
00:06:56,283 --> 00:07:00,218
THIS IS INTERESTING.
SHIPPING INVOICE,
NO RETURN ADDRESS.

117
00:07:00,286 --> 00:07:02,621
<i> JUST A WEB SITE.</i>

118
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:07,058
LUSTYFUN.COM.
THIS IS WHERE JAROD
ORDERED ALL THE STUFF FROM.

119
00:07:07,127 --> 00:07:09,660
FIND A REAL ADDRESS ON THAT.
AND, BROOTS, NOT A WORD.

120
00:07:09,729 --> 00:07:12,063
BUT MR. LYLE JUST SAID
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO--
BROOTS.

121
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,633
THINK OF YOUR
WORST NIGHTMARE.

122
00:07:24,544 --> 00:07:26,745
[ Cracks Whip ]

123
00:07:31,885 --> 00:07:35,519
<i> MIGHTY BOBCATS</i>
<i> FROM MARRIETTA UNIVERSITY.</i>

124
00:07:35,588 --> 00:07:39,223
YOU MUST REALLY LIKE
THESE MIGHTY BOBCATS.

125
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:41,926
YOU'RE A THERAPIST.
YOU CAN USE THE TERM OBSESSION.

126
00:07:41,995 --> 00:07:44,496
DON'T YOU HAVE
A SIMILAR ATTACHMENT
TO YOUR ALMA MATER?

127
00:07:44,564 --> 00:07:46,498
I HAVE A STRONG FEELING
ABOUT THE PLACE.

128
00:07:46,566 --> 00:07:50,768
PLEASE. JAROD, I WANT
TO THANK YOU FOR STEPPING IN
ON SHORT NOTICE...

129
00:07:50,837 --> 00:07:53,371
<i>AND TAKING OVER</i>
<i>FOR DR. BLASS.</i>

130
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:56,374
I HAVE TO TELL YOU,
I'M CONCERNED ABOUT
DR. BLASS'S PATIENTS,

131
00:07:56,443 --> 00:07:58,743
HOW THEY'RE GOING TO
MAKE THE TRANSITION TO YOU.

132
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:01,246
MANY HAVE SPENT A LONG TIME
DEVELOPING A TRUST WITH HER.

133
00:08:01,315 --> 00:08:03,948
WELL, I'M GOING TO
HAVE TO WORK VERY HARD
TO MAINTAIN THAT TRUST.

134
00:08:04,017 --> 00:08:07,752
YOU NEVER REALIZE HOW MANY LIVES
ARE AFFECTED WHEN A TRAGEDY
LIKE MELISSA'S HAPPENS.

135
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:10,588
HAS HER ATTACKER
BEEN CAUGHT YET?

136
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:15,960
NO. POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR
ONE OF HER COURT REFERRAL
PATIENTS-- LUKE CARLO.

137
00:08:16,029 --> 00:08:18,963
<i>MELISSA WAS WORKING WITH HIM</i>
<i>AS A TERM OF HIS PROBATION.</i>

138
00:08:19,032 --> 00:08:20,899
WHAT HAPPENED?

139
00:08:20,967 --> 00:08:23,868
MELISSA HAD
THE ADMIRABLE TENDENCY
TO CARE TOO MUCH.

140
00:08:23,937 --> 00:08:26,804
<i>CARLO WAS A PREDATOR.</i>
<i>HE TOOK ADVANTAGE OF THAT.</i>

141
00:08:26,873 --> 00:08:29,807
<i>HE CALLED HER,</i>
<i>SAID HE WAS HAVING A CRISIS.</i>

142
00:08:29,876 --> 00:08:32,610
<i>SHE ENDED UP DOWNTOWN</i>
<i>IN SOME DIVE CALLED</i>
<i>THE EROS INN.</i>

143
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,812
<i> I HEAR SHE'S IN</i>
<i> PRETTY BAD SHAPE.</i>

144
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:36,815
<i>SHE'S A SHELL</i>
<i>OF WHO SHE WAS.</i>

145
00:08:36,883 --> 00:08:40,885
I JUST WISH THAT
YOU COULD HAVE MET THE MELISSA
THAT WE ALL USED TO KNOW.

146
00:08:40,953 --> 00:08:42,920
<i>SHE WAS A WONDERFUL,</i>
<i>LOVING WOMAN.</i>

147
00:09:02,309 --> 00:09:04,875
<i>[ Dr. Arnett On Tape ]</i>
<i>MR. TRULY,</i>
<i>DO YOU KNOW WHY YOU'RE HERE?</i>

148
00:09:04,944 --> 00:09:07,312
<i> YEAH. JUDGE DETTMAN</i>
<i> THINKS I'M A PERVERT.</i>

149
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:12,483
TONY?

150
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:14,485
I'M DR. KINSEY.
I'M THE NEW GUY.

151
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:18,656
SO, I UNDERSTAND YOU'RE
THE ONE WHO KNOWS EVERYTHING
THAT GOES ON AROUND HERE.

152
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:21,492
YEAH. I LIVE
THE LOWLY LIFE OF AN INTERN.
I'M ALSO WORKIN' ON MY MASTER'S.

153
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:23,795
<i> "PSYCHO-SEXUAL AGGRESSION."</i>

154
00:09:23,864 --> 00:09:27,332
<i> "ABERRANT SEXUAL BEHAVIOR."</i>
HMM. CHEERY STUFF.

155
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:31,702
<i>MY HONOR'S THESIS IS ON</i>
<i>SEXUAL PREDATORS, AND I WATCH</i>
<i>ALL THE COURT REFERRED SESSIONS,</i>

156
00:09:31,771 --> 00:09:34,472
SO I MIGHT AS WELL
MAKE GOOD USE OF IT.

157
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:36,975
-<i> IS THIS DR. ARNETT</i>
<i> WORKING WITH SOMEONE?</i>
-<i> YEAH.</i>

158
00:09:37,044 --> 00:09:39,477
THIS IS YOUR
STANDARD TRENCH COAT
AND SNEAKER FLASHER. HERE.

159
00:09:39,545 --> 00:09:42,313
<i>[ Dr. Arnett ]</i>
<i>EVERYONE HAS FEARS.</i>
<i>IT'S NOTHING TO BE ASHAMED OF.</i>

160
00:09:42,382 --> 00:09:45,350
THE KEY IS TO ACKNOWLEDGE
AND UNDERSTAND THEM.

161
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:47,351
YEAH, WELL, I'M NOT AFRAID
OF ANYTHING.

162
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:50,454
<i>[ Tony ] IT'S AMAZING WHAT</i>
<i>YOU CAN LEARN ABOUT A PERSON'S</i>
<i>PSYCHE BY JUST WATCHING THEM.</i>

163
00:09:50,523 --> 00:09:54,859
<i>MR. TRULY, WHEN I WAS A KID,</i>
<i>MY FATHER TOOK ME DUCK HUNTING.</i>

164
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:58,063
I WAS LAYING OUT THE DECOYS
AND SOMEHOW THE BOAT FLIPPED.

165
00:09:58,131 --> 00:10:00,631
I GOT TRAPPED UNDERNEATH
IN THIS TINY AIR POCKET.

166
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:04,702
<i>THE WATER KEPT RISING</i>
<i>UP MY NECK, OVER MY CHIN.</i>

167
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:08,773
I WAS TERRIFIED.
I NEARLY DROWNED.

168
00:10:10,376 --> 00:10:12,844
TO THIS DAY,
I'M HYDROPHOBIC.

169
00:10:12,913 --> 00:10:15,579
<i>A SHOWER, FINE.</i>
<i>BUT A BATH, A SWIMMING POOL,</i>

170
00:10:15,649 --> 00:10:17,915
THE FEAR RISES IN ME
AS FAST AS THE WATER.

171
00:10:17,984 --> 00:10:21,019
<i> SEE, FEAR IS NATURAL.</i>
<i> IT'S HEALTHY EVEN.</i>

172
00:10:21,087 --> 00:10:25,590
BUT WE'VE GOT TO CONTROL IT.
WE CAN'T LET "IT" CONTROL US.

173
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:29,560
DID YOU OBSERVE
DR. BLASS'S SESSIONS
WITH LUKE CARLO?

174
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:33,698
THE GUY THAT ASSAULTED HER?
YEAH. THERE ARE TAPES
OF THAT GUY IN HER OFFICE.

175
00:10:33,767 --> 00:10:36,835
SCARY DUDE.
HE WAS THE KIND OF GUY
THAT WAS JUST WOUND TOO TIGHT.

176
00:10:36,903 --> 00:10:41,706
<i>UNFORTUNATELY FOR DR. BLASS,</i>
<i>HE DECIDED THAT SHE WAS GONNA</i>
<i>BE THE ONE THAT HE WENT OFF ON.</i>

177
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:59,390
INTERESTING DRAWING,
BROOTS.

178
00:10:59,459 --> 00:11:02,393
[ Clears Throat ]
OH, I WAS JUST DOODLING.
IT'S NOTHING.

179
00:11:02,462 --> 00:11:07,231
WELL, DOODLING IS OFTEN
THE MOST DIRECT EXPRESSION
OF THE UNCONSCIOUS.

180
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:11,936
<i>AND I COULDN'T HELP NOTICE</i>
<i>THERE WAS A CERTAIN RESEMBLANCE</i>
<i>TO MISS PARKER.</i>

181
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:16,140
YEAH? WELL, IT'S JUST
THAT SHE'S SO IMPRESSIVE.

182
00:11:16,209 --> 00:11:20,211
YOU KNOW, THE WAY
SHE'S ALWAYS IN CONTROL.
THE WAY SHE NEVER SHOWS FEAR.

183
00:11:21,782 --> 00:11:23,982
OH, GOD.

184
00:11:24,051 --> 00:11:28,286
FANTASIES ABOUT COWORKERS
ARE PERFECTLY NATURAL, BROOTS.

185
00:11:28,355 --> 00:11:32,590
I'D BE VERY SURPRISED
IF SUBLIMATED SEXUAL FEELINGS...

186
00:11:32,659 --> 00:11:35,893
- DIDN'T SURFACE
FROM TIME TO TIME.
- SO, WHAT DO I DO?

187
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:40,097
WELL, YOU CAN'T KEEP
THESE EMOTIONS INSIDE.

188
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:42,733
OTHERWISE THEY'LL,
UH, CONTROL YOU.

189
00:11:42,802 --> 00:11:46,171
OH, NO.
I'M NOT GONNA TELL HER.

190
00:11:46,239 --> 00:11:48,605
TELL HER WHAT?
ANOTHER CRUSH, BROOTS?

191
00:11:48,674 --> 00:11:52,309
WHO IS IT THIS TIME?
THAT DOUBLE-CHINNED CHICK
IN, UH, R & D?

192
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:54,278
[ Chuckles ]
NO. YEAH.

193
00:11:54,347 --> 00:11:58,182
<i> UH, YEAH.</i>
<i> BUT IT'S TWO, UH,</i>
<i> CLEFTS, ONE CHIN.</i>

194
00:11:59,886 --> 00:12:03,154
- ♪♪ [ Music On Computer ]
- OH, LOOK.

195
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:06,290
IT'S THE ADDRESS
FOR JAROD'S RECEIPT--
LUSTYFUN.COM.

196
00:12:06,359 --> 00:12:09,493
<i>ALL RIGHT, BROOTS,</i>
<i>YOU STAY HERE AND PRETEND</i>
<i>LIKE WE'RE STILL SEARCHING.</i>

197
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:12,363
- OKAY.
- THE LESS LYLE KNOWS,
THE BETTER.

198
00:12:12,432 --> 00:12:15,199
AREN'T WE SUPPOSED TO
REPORT EVERYTHING WE HEAR?

199
00:12:15,268 --> 00:12:17,801
AREN'T YOU SUPPOSED
TO HAVE A PAIR?

200
00:12:17,871 --> 00:12:19,837
UH, MISS PARKER,
I'LL STAY.

201
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:22,273
<i> I HAVE PLENTY OF THINGS</i>
<i> TO DO HERE.</i>

202
00:12:22,342 --> 00:12:25,175
IT'S YOU AND ME, COWBOY.
SADDLE UP.

203
00:12:26,713 --> 00:12:29,680
GOOD LUCK, BROOTS.

204
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:32,283
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>I DON'T KNOW, DOCTOR.</i>
<i>I'M JUST SO CONFUSED.</i>

205
00:12:32,352 --> 00:12:35,186
<i>I NEVER HAD TO DEAL</i>
<i>WITH ANYTHING LIKE THIS BEFORE.</i>

206
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:38,822
<i>[ Woman #2 ]</i>
<i>GLORIA, IT WILL BE FINE,</i>
<i>I PROMISE YOU.</i>

207
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:41,292
<i>WE'RE GONNA GET YOU</i>
<i>THROUGH THIS.</i>
DR. BLASS?

208
00:12:41,361 --> 00:12:44,061
OH, DR. KINSEY.

209
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:48,199
I'M SORRY. I JUST NEEDED
TO LOOK AT THESE OLD TAPES.

210
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:51,970
I HEARD YOUR VOICE.
YOU WERE ONE OF
DR. BLASS'S PATIENTS?

211
00:12:52,038 --> 00:12:56,407
OH, WELL, SHE-- SHE WAS JUST,
UH, HELPING ME WITH A PROBLEM
I HAD WITH MY BOYFRIEND, EDDIE.

212
00:12:56,476 --> 00:12:59,010
I-I JUST WANTED TO HEAR
HER ADVICE AGAIN.

213
00:12:59,078 --> 00:13:01,479
<i>THERE'S NO ONE ELSE LIKE HER.</i>
<i>EXCUSE ME.</i>
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

214
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:10,988
[ Tape Starts, Rewinding ]

215
00:13:11,057 --> 00:13:16,060
GLORIA, IT WILL BE FINE.
I PROMISE YOU, WE'RE GONNA
GET YOU THROUGH THIS.

216
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:21,332
THANK YOU.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
I'D DO WITHOUT YOU.

217
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,735
OH.

218
00:13:30,777 --> 00:13:33,043
<i>[ Dog Barking In Distance ]</i>

219
00:13:52,932 --> 00:13:56,166
[ Doorbell Rings ]

220
00:13:58,571 --> 00:14:00,504
PUT THE PACKAGE IN THE BOX.

221
00:14:00,574 --> 00:14:02,506
OH, I'M NOT A DELIVERYMAN,
DR. BLASS.

222
00:14:02,575 --> 00:14:05,142
I'M A DOCTOR WITH THE CLINIC.

223
00:14:05,211 --> 00:14:07,111
GO AWAY.
I DON'T NEED YOUR HELP.

224
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:09,780
WELL, ACTUALLY, I WAS
HOPING TO GET YOUR HELP.

225
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:12,850
<i>YOU SEE, I'M TAKING OVER</i>
<i>YOUR CASE LOAD AT THE CLINIC.</i>

226
00:14:12,918 --> 00:14:15,853
THERE'S A NEW PATIENT
I NEED SOME ADVICE WITH.

227
00:14:15,922 --> 00:14:19,690
<i>A YOUNG WOMAN.</i>
<i>I NEED TO REACH HER BEFORE</i>
<i>SHE SLIPS OVER THE EDGE.</i>

228
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,832
<i> [ Lock Clicks ]</i>

229
00:14:31,137 --> 00:14:33,471
I REALLY WISH I COULD HELP.
I, UH, DON'T PRACTICE ANYMORE.

230
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:36,006
MAYBE NOT, BUT I'M HOPING
YOU STILL CARE.

231
00:14:39,813 --> 00:14:41,912
HOW DO I KNOW YOU REALLY ARE
WHO YOU SAY YOU ARE?

232
00:14:41,981 --> 00:14:45,149
MY NAME IS
DR. JAROD KINSEY.

233
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:50,087
DR. ARNETT HIRED ME.
I WORK WITH DR. COVNEY,
AND TONY IS THE INTERN.

234
00:14:50,156 --> 00:14:52,423
BUT ANYBODY
COULD KNOW THAT.

235
00:14:52,492 --> 00:14:55,526
WELL, YOU'RE RIGHT.
BUT, UH, GLORIA,

236
00:14:55,594 --> 00:14:59,130
SHE'S STILL HAVING PROBLEMS
WITH HER BOYFRIEND, EDDIE.

237
00:14:59,199 --> 00:15:01,466
[ Clicks Tongue ]
GLORIA.

238
00:15:01,534 --> 00:15:05,035
PLEASE? I WON'T TAKE UP
TOO MUCH OF YOUR TIME.

239
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:21,619
YOU COLLECT SHELLS.
DO YOU LIKE THE OCEAN?

240
00:15:21,688 --> 00:15:23,922
MY GRANDMOTHER
HAD A BEACH HOUSE
WHEN I WAS GROWING UP.

241
00:15:23,991 --> 00:15:28,292
SHE WAS MY SANCTUARY.
I GUESS THE OCEAN
STILL REMINDS ME OF HER.

242
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:31,730
I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO PUT ON SOME TEA.

243
00:15:34,668 --> 00:15:38,403
<i>SO, YOU SAID SOMETHING</i>
<i>ABOUT A NEW PATIENT?</i>

244
00:15:38,471 --> 00:15:42,574
YES. SHE'S SUFFERING
FROM A GENERALIZED
ANXIETY DISORDER...

245
00:15:42,642 --> 00:15:44,642
BROUGHT ON
BY EMOTIONAL TRAUMA.

246
00:15:44,711 --> 00:15:47,311
SYMPTOMS?

247
00:15:47,380 --> 00:15:51,383
<i>INSOMNIA, PANIC ATTACKS</i>
<i>AND AN OVERWHELMING</i>
<i>SENSE OF FEAR.</i>

248
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:56,621
THE THING IS, DEEP DOWN INSIDE,
I THINK SHE REALLY WANTS
TO GET BETTER,

249
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:58,823
BUT THE FEAR STOPS HER.

250
00:15:58,891 --> 00:16:02,160
<i>SOME DAYS SHE'S TOO SCARED</i>
<i>TO EVEN GET OUT OF BED.</i>

251
00:16:02,228 --> 00:16:04,963
<i>HER HEART RACES,</i>
<i>SHE CAN'T BREATHE.</i>

252
00:16:05,032 --> 00:16:08,132
SHE FEELS LIKE
SHE'S LOSING CONTROL.

253
00:16:08,201 --> 00:16:10,501
<i>THE THING THAT</i>
<i>REALLY WORRIES ME IS</i>
<i>SHE'S BEGINNING TO THINK...</i>

254
00:16:10,570 --> 00:16:13,971
THAT ENDING IT ALL
IS THE ONLY WAY OUT.

255
00:16:22,082 --> 00:16:24,082
THERE'S NO NEW PATIENT,
IS THERE?

256
00:16:25,852 --> 00:16:28,953
LIKE I TOLD YOU BEFORE,
I DON'T WANT YOUR HELP.

257
00:16:29,022 --> 00:16:32,257
MAYBE IF YOU JUST TALKED ABOUT
THE NIGHT YOU WERE ATTACKED?

258
00:16:33,493 --> 00:16:37,028
- NO, I CAN'T.
- JUST TRY.

259
00:16:37,097 --> 00:16:40,966
LOOK, MY HEAD IS ALL
JUST TWISTED AND JUMBLED.
MELISSA?

260
00:16:42,101 --> 00:16:44,469
JUST TRY.

261
00:16:49,976 --> 00:16:54,445
I WENT DOWNTOWN TO THIS HOTEL
ONE OF MY PA-- ONE OF MY
PATIENTS WAS STAYING IN.

262
00:16:54,514 --> 00:16:56,447
<i> LUKE CARLO.</i>

263
00:16:56,516 --> 00:16:59,183
THE DOOR WAS OPEN,
SO I WALKED IN.

264
00:16:59,252 --> 00:17:04,488
THERE WAS A... HAND
CLAMPED OVER MY MOUTH.

265
00:17:04,558 --> 00:17:08,626
<i> AND... A BLINDFOLD.</i>

266
00:17:12,098 --> 00:17:14,732
HANDCUFFS.

267
00:17:14,801 --> 00:17:18,936
HANDCUFFS WITH LUKE CARLO'S
FINGERPRINTS ON THEM?

268
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:22,373
[ Breathing Heavily ]
<i> [ Pills Rattling ]</i>

269
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:25,510
LUKE. I THOUGHT HE WAS
GETTING BETTER, YOU KNOW?

270
00:17:25,578 --> 00:17:28,980
I THOUGHT
I WAS HELPING HIM.

271
00:17:29,049 --> 00:17:33,017
- YOU HAVE TO GO NOW.
- IT'S NOT A VERY GOOD IDEA
FOR YOU TO MIX THOSE THINGS.

272
00:17:33,086 --> 00:17:35,052
I KNOW THAT.
CAN YOU PLEASE JUST GO?

273
00:17:35,121 --> 00:17:37,855
- WE SHOULD JUST GO SIT--
- PLEASE GO!

274
00:17:37,924 --> 00:17:40,258
OKAY. OKAY.

275
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:50,735
<i>IT'S NOT LIKE I EVER</i>
<i>HURT ANYBODY. I JUST</i>
<i>LIKE TO LOOK, ALL RIGHT?</i>

276
00:17:50,804 --> 00:17:54,538
NO, IT IS NOT ALL RIGHT.
YOU ARE VICTIMIZING THESE WOMEN.

277
00:17:54,607 --> 00:17:57,408
SO WHAT WE HAVE TO DO
IS FIND A BETTER WAY...

278
00:17:57,477 --> 00:18:00,111
<i>FOR YOU TO DEAL</i>
<i>WITH YOUR SEXUAL IMPULSES.</i>

279
00:18:00,179 --> 00:18:02,113
DEAL WITH THEM.

280
00:18:02,182 --> 00:18:06,250
LADY, YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT IT'S LIKE
IN MY NEIGHBORHOOD.

281
00:18:06,319 --> 00:18:11,289
<i> AROUND HERE,</i>
<i> SEX IS ALL SECRETS</i>
<i> AND WHISPERS.</i>

282
00:18:11,358 --> 00:18:16,093
THERE IT'S SOLD IN THE STREETS.
IT'S IN YOUR FACE 24-7.

283
00:18:16,162 --> 00:18:19,296
IT DOESN'T TAKE A GENIUS
TO FIGURE OUT WHY THEY CALL IT
THE "FLESH DISTRICT."

284
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:22,801
[ Rewinding ]
IT DOESN'T TAKE A GENIUS...

285
00:18:22,869 --> 00:18:25,436
TO FIGURE OUT WHY THEY CALL IT
THE "FLESH DISTRICT."

286
00:18:25,505 --> 00:18:29,073
<i> THE "FLESH DISTRICT."</i>
<i> THE "FLESH DISTRICT."</i>

287
00:18:38,485 --> 00:18:41,553
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

288
00:18:53,466 --> 00:18:56,567
EXCUSE ME.
I'M LOOKING FOR THIS GUY.

289
00:18:58,905 --> 00:19:00,805
I DON'T SEE NOBODY.

290
00:19:00,874 --> 00:19:04,241
NOBODY SEES YOU.
THE BEST EYES TO SEE THE WORLD
WITH ARE INVISIBLE.

291
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:06,744
YOU'VE SPENT SOME TIME
ON THE STREETS.

292
00:19:06,813 --> 00:19:10,448
YOU COULD SAY THAT.
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
A REGULAR AROUND HERE.

293
00:19:10,517 --> 00:19:12,583
WALKED BY HERE
JUST A MINUTE AGO.

294
00:19:12,652 --> 00:19:14,585
<i> I SEE HIM AROUND HERE</i>
<i> ALL THE TIME.</i>

295
00:19:14,654 --> 00:19:17,622
WHEN IN DOUBT, LIQUOR STORE
DOWN THE STREET.

296
00:19:17,691 --> 00:19:20,024
- THERE HE IS, RIGHT THERE.
- THANKS.

297
00:19:24,597 --> 00:19:26,798
[ Clattering ]

298
00:19:30,036 --> 00:19:31,870
<i>WHAT DO YOU WANT WITH ME?</i>

299
00:19:31,938 --> 00:19:34,472
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT DR. BLASS.

300
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:36,541
I DIDN'T HAVE NOTHIN'
TO DO WITH THAT.

301
00:19:36,609 --> 00:19:39,644
- IS THAT WHY YOU'RE
POINTING A GUN AT ME?
- I DIDN'T DO IT.

302
00:19:39,713 --> 00:19:43,147
<i> I'M TELLIN' YOU.</i>
<i> I DIDN'T... DO IT!</i>

303
00:19:44,684 --> 00:19:46,617
I DIDN'T DO IT!

304
00:19:51,624 --> 00:19:54,925
THIS ISN'T SLEAZY.
IT'S BEAVER CLEAVER'S HOUSE.

305
00:19:54,994 --> 00:19:58,563
THIS IS NOT EXACTLY
WHAT I WOULD HAVE EXPECTED
FROM LUSTYFUN.COM.

306
00:19:58,632 --> 00:20:02,767
BEHIND ALL
THE ALUMINUM SIDING,
SUBURBIA'S A FREAK SHOW.

307
00:20:04,104 --> 00:20:06,871
MISS PARKER,
CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?

308
00:20:09,042 --> 00:20:13,144
YOU SEE, SYDNEY
HAS THIS THEORY ABOUT
EXPRESSING YOUR FEELINGS,

309
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:15,747
NOT BOTTLING UP
YOUR EMOTIONS.

310
00:20:15,815 --> 00:20:17,749
IS THIS MORE ABOUT
YOU AND THE CHINS?

311
00:20:17,817 --> 00:20:19,751
YEAH. UH, NO.

312
00:20:19,820 --> 00:20:21,920
<i> [ Doorbell Rings ]</i>
WELL, KIND OF.
BROOTS.

313
00:20:21,988 --> 00:20:26,290
NO WOMAN WORTH HER SALT WANTS
TO BE WITH A GUY WHO SPILLS
HIS FEELINGS ALL OVER THE FLOOR.

314
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:29,560
YOU LIKE THIS CHICK,
EITHER MAKE A MOVE
OR MOVE ON.

315
00:20:31,964 --> 00:20:34,999
<i> [ Door Opens ]</i>
HI. WE'RE HERE TO SHOP.

316
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:40,771
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKIN' ABOUT.
- SOMETHING EXOTIC FOR HUBBY?

317
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,775
- [ Sniffs ]
- I'M AFRAID I CAN'T HELP YOU.

318
00:20:45,178 --> 00:20:47,111
I GUESS JAROD LIED
TO US, HONEY.

319
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:50,280
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
YOU'RE FRIENDS OF JAROD'S?

320
00:20:50,349 --> 00:20:53,151
COME ON IN!
[ Chuckles ]

321
00:20:55,555 --> 00:20:59,357
SORRY ABOUT THE HASSLE.
GOTTA KEEP A LOW PROFILE
FOR THE NEIGHBORS.

322
00:20:59,425 --> 00:21:02,226
THIS IS MY WIFE, LINDA.
I'M ROY.

323
00:21:02,295 --> 00:21:04,695
GOD BLESS THE INTERNET.

324
00:21:04,764 --> 00:21:09,667
A FEW MONTHS AGO--
SEX TOYS, EXPERIMENTING--
IT WAS JUST A HOBBY WITH US.

325
00:21:09,736 --> 00:21:11,969
OF COURSE,
I DON'T HAVE TO TELL YOU TWO
ABOUT THAT, NOW DO I?

326
00:21:12,037 --> 00:21:13,971
MMM. IT'D BE NICE
IF YOU DIDN'T.

327
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:16,741
SO, UH, ROY,
HOW DO YOU KNOW JAROD?

328
00:21:16,810 --> 00:21:20,545
<i>NEVER MET. EXCEPT IN CHAT ROOMS</i>
<i>AND THE HUMONGOUS ORDER</i>
<i>HE LAID ON US.</i>

329
00:21:20,613 --> 00:21:23,080
IT GOT MY WIFE'S ATTENTION,
I CAN TELL YOU THAT.

330
00:21:23,149 --> 00:21:25,149
<i> [ Chuckles ]</i>
<i> YEAH, WE'RE STILL SHIPPIN'</i>
<i> HIM STUFF ON BACK ORDER.</i>

331
00:21:25,218 --> 00:21:28,553
REALLY? YOU KNOW,
HE JUST RECENTLY MOVED.

332
00:21:28,622 --> 00:21:31,455
- YOU DON'T HAPPEN TO HAVE
HIS NEW ADDRESS, DO YOU?
- WELL, YEAH.

333
00:21:31,524 --> 00:21:34,125
I THINK HE GAVE IT
TO US, YEAH.

334
00:21:36,696 --> 00:21:41,265
YEAH.
1248 WREN PARK, WYATTVILLE.

335
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:44,769
YEAH, 1248 WREN PARK.
THAT-- THAT'S IT.

336
00:21:44,838 --> 00:21:47,672
WHY DON'T YOU TWO COME
INTO THE DEN. WE'LL OPEN UP
THE SLOE GIN...

337
00:21:47,741 --> 00:21:50,742
AND SEE WHAT KIND OF
NATURAL WONDERS OCCUR?

338
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:54,878
[ Chuckles ]
I PREFER MY NATURAL WONDERS IN
NATIONAL PARKS. BUT THANK YOU.

339
00:21:54,947 --> 00:21:57,147
OH, COME ON, I JUST LAID
SOME BRAND-NEW SHAG.

340
00:21:57,216 --> 00:21:59,917
IT'S THREE-QUARTER PILE,
EXTRA THICK PADDING.

341
00:21:59,986 --> 00:22:02,019
MAKES FOR SOME
COMFY CUDDLIN'.

342
00:22:02,087 --> 00:22:04,989
ARE YOU TALKIN'
ABOUT THE FOUR OF US?
YOU TWO SWING, DON'T YA?

343
00:22:05,058 --> 00:22:07,858
- [ Broots Chuckles ]
-<i> VERY TEMPTING, ROY.</i>

344
00:22:07,927 --> 00:22:11,262
HOWEVER, I COULD NEVER SHARE
THIS STUD MUFFIN WITH ANYONE.
MAYBE NEXT TIME.

345
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:14,699
- [ Miss Parker ]
BUH-BYE.
-<i> [ Door Opens, Closes ]</i>

346
00:22:14,767 --> 00:22:17,034
<i> [ Phone Beeping ]</i>

347
00:22:19,505 --> 00:22:22,140
YEAH, IT'S ME.
THEY JUST LEFT.

348
00:22:23,743 --> 00:22:26,577
<i> JAROD?</i>
<i> I HEARD YOU WENT TO SEE</i>
<i> MELISSA LAST NIGHT.</i>

349
00:22:26,646 --> 00:22:28,812
YES, I DID.
I'M SURPRISED
YOU GOT IN.

350
00:22:28,881 --> 00:22:30,815
MOST OF THE TIME
SHE'S NOT EVEN
ANSWERING THE PHONE.

351
00:22:30,884 --> 00:22:33,417
HOW IS SHE?
SHE'S NOT DOING WELL.

352
00:22:33,486 --> 00:22:37,288
SHE'S OBVIOUSLY PARANOID
AND SHE'S EXHIBITING
OBSESSIVE-COMPULSIVE BEHAVIOR.

353
00:22:37,357 --> 00:22:39,657
<i>NOW I REALIZE</i>
<i>SHE'S BEEN TRAUMATIZED,</i>

354
00:22:39,726 --> 00:22:42,894
BUT I'M SENSING THERE'S
SOMETHING, SOMETHING ELSE
GOING ON WITH HER.

355
00:22:42,962 --> 00:22:45,296
SO, YOU THINK THERE
COULD BE DEEPER ISSUES AT WORK?

356
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:48,900
PERHAPS. I'M NOT SURE.
I WAS HOPING MAYBE
YOU COULD TELL ME.

357
00:22:48,968 --> 00:22:53,404
UP UNTIL ALL THIS, MELISSA BLASS
WAS ONE OF THE MOST SOLID,
STABLE PEOPLE I'VE EVER KNOWN.

358
00:22:58,043 --> 00:23:00,477
[ Doorbell Rings ]

359
00:23:01,781 --> 00:23:04,915
JAROD, PLEASE.
I DON'T WANT TO TALK.

360
00:23:04,984 --> 00:23:07,818
I HAVE A DELIVERY THIS TIME.

361
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:17,160
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO
TAKE A WALK ON THE BEACH?

362
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:26,570
[ Waves Crashing,
Seagulls Squawking ]

363
00:23:31,410 --> 00:23:33,677
JAROD, THIS IS CRAZY.

364
00:23:33,747 --> 00:23:37,881
<i> WE'RE SHRINKS.</i>
<i> CRAZY IS OUR BUSINESS.</i>

365
00:23:37,951 --> 00:23:40,718
I WANT YOU
TO CLOSE YOUR EYES.

366
00:23:40,787 --> 00:23:43,187
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

367
00:23:44,724 --> 00:23:48,425
IMAGINE YOURSELF
AT YOUR GRANDMOTHER'S
BEACH HOUSE.

368
00:23:48,494 --> 00:23:53,197
REMEMBER HOW SAFE
YOU USED TO FEEL THERE.

369
00:23:55,201 --> 00:23:57,768
HEAR THE SURF
ROLLING IN AND OUT.

370
00:23:57,836 --> 00:24:00,971
FEEL THE WARM SUN
ON YOUR FACE.

371
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:04,375
NOTHING BAD CAN EVER
HAPPEN TO YOU HERE.

372
00:24:04,444 --> 00:24:06,844
<i>[ Melissa's Voice ]</i>
<i>AND SO I WALKED IN.</i>

373
00:24:06,912 --> 00:24:09,613
<i>THERE WAS A HAND</i>
<i>CLAMPED OVER MY MOUTH.</i>

374
00:24:09,682 --> 00:24:13,351
<i>BLINDFOLD. HANDCUFFS.</i>

375
00:24:13,419 --> 00:24:17,221
-<i> HANDCUFFS. HANDCUFFS.</i>
- JAROD, I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

376
00:24:17,290 --> 00:24:20,825
I USE SENSORY-RELAXATION
EXERCISES ALL THE TIME
WITH MY PATIENTS.

377
00:24:20,893 --> 00:24:24,061
AND YOU KNOW
THAT THEY WORK.

378
00:24:24,130 --> 00:24:28,132
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT
THAT WE TALK ABOUT THE NIGHT
YOU WERE ATTACKED.

379
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:30,768
BUT I TOLD YOU
EVERYTHING I COULD.

380
00:24:30,837 --> 00:24:35,572
I NEED TO KNOW IF YOU
ACTUALLY SAW LUKE CARLO.

381
00:24:35,641 --> 00:24:37,674
DID YOU ACTUALLY
SEE HIM?

382
00:24:37,744 --> 00:24:40,344
[ Breathing Heavily ]
WELL, HE CALLED ME
AND LURED ME DOWN THERE.

383
00:24:40,413 --> 00:24:42,780
BUT DID YOU SEE HIM?

384
00:24:44,851 --> 00:24:47,251
WELL, I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T REMEMBER. I--

385
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:49,253
-<i> [ Pills Rattling ]</i>
- NO.

386
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:51,355
I GUESS I--
I MEAN I NEVER--
NO, I DIDN'T.

387
00:24:51,424 --> 00:24:54,358
<i>BUT WHY WOULD ANYONE ELSE</i>
<i>WANT ME THERE?</i>

388
00:24:54,426 --> 00:24:57,295
DAMN IT! OH!

389
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:08,005
PRONIL?
<i>JUST A MILD SEDATIVE.</i>

390
00:25:08,074 --> 00:25:10,140
DR. COVNEY FILLED THIS?

391
00:25:10,209 --> 00:25:12,476
HE HANDLES ALL THE MEDS
AT THE CLINIC.

392
00:25:48,881 --> 00:25:51,648
OH, HEY, JAROD.
DR. COVNEY.

393
00:25:51,717 --> 00:25:55,319
SOMETHING WRONG?
HOW OFTEN ARE MISTAKES MADE
ON PRESCRIPTIONS AROUND HERE?

394
00:25:55,388 --> 00:25:58,655
NEVER. WHY?
BECAUSE THIS WAS GIVEN
TO A PATIENT...

395
00:25:58,724 --> 00:26:02,759
- IN A BOTTLE MARKED "PRONIL."
- DARONEX? WELL, THIS IS WRONG.

396
00:26:02,828 --> 00:26:05,596
THIS IS REALLY WRONG.
PRONIL'S A SEDATIVE.

397
00:26:05,665 --> 00:26:07,665
BUT DARONEX--
ITS MAIN SIDE EFFECT
IS HEIGHTENED ANXIETY.

398
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:10,100
A STEADY DIET OF THESE
WILL PUSH JUST ABOUT ANYBODY
OVER THE EDGE.

399
00:26:10,169 --> 00:26:12,670
THEN EXPLAIN TO ME
WHY YOU GAVE IT
TO MELISSA BLASS?

400
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:16,240
MELISSA? NOW WAIT A MINUTE.
I DID NOT FILL
THAT PRESCRIPTION.

401
00:26:16,308 --> 00:26:18,242
YOUR NAME'S ON THE BOTTLE.
I'M THE ONE
WITH THE MED PERMIT.

402
00:26:18,311 --> 00:26:22,546
MY NAME IS ON ALL THE LABELS.
BUT I DIDN'T FILL THAT ONE.
DR. ARNETT DID.

403
00:26:22,615 --> 00:26:24,748
<i>HE TAKES CARE OF</i>
<i>MELISSA'S MEDS PERSONALLY.</i>

404
00:26:24,817 --> 00:26:28,519
BUT I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE'D MAKE A MISTAKE LIKE THAT.

405
00:26:30,290 --> 00:26:33,090
<i> NEITHER CAN I.</i>

406
00:26:38,898 --> 00:26:41,565
<i> WE TRIED</i>
<i> WHAT YOU SUGGESTED,</i>
<i> DR. KINSEY.</i>

407
00:26:41,634 --> 00:26:45,736
MAKING LOVE AT HOME,
BEHIND CLOSED DOORS,
IN YOUR OWN BEDROOM.

408
00:26:45,805 --> 00:26:49,106
YEAH. IT WAS GOOD.

409
00:26:49,175 --> 00:26:51,842
UNFORTUNATELY, I GOT
A LITTLE OUT OF CONTROL.
I COULDN'T HELP MYSELF.

410
00:26:51,911 --> 00:26:55,045
I OPENED THE CURTAINS.
AND THEN IT GOT GREAT.

411
00:26:55,114 --> 00:26:58,182
WE HAD NO IDEA WE HAD
SO MANY NICE NEIGHBORS
IN OUR APARTMENT COMPLEX.

412
00:26:58,251 --> 00:27:01,952
<i>IT'S REALLY A SHAME</i>
<i>WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO MOVE NOW.</i>

413
00:27:03,823 --> 00:27:07,157
GIVE ME AN "S"! "S"!
GIVE ME AN "E"! "E"!

414
00:27:07,227 --> 00:27:09,159
GIVE ME AN "X"! "X"!

415
00:27:09,228 --> 00:27:12,763
SEX!
[ Giggles ]

416
00:27:12,832 --> 00:27:16,000
<i> THANK YOU, MONIQUE.</i>
<i> NOW, PLEASE PUT</i>
<i> YOUR CLOTHES ON.</i>

417
00:27:20,105 --> 00:27:23,441
WELL, THIS IS
THE ADDRESS WE GOT FROM
THAT LUSTYFUN.COM COUPLE.

418
00:27:25,911 --> 00:27:27,711
<i>IT'S NOT THE NICEST PLACE</i>
<i>JAROD'S EVER LIVED.</i>

419
00:27:27,780 --> 00:27:30,914
BETTER THAN
SWINGER'S CENTRAL.

420
00:27:30,983 --> 00:27:33,950
COME HERE.

421
00:27:34,019 --> 00:27:36,754
YEAH.
GIVE ME A BOOST.

422
00:27:38,591 --> 00:27:40,824
BROOTS?
OH, YEAH, OKAY, RIGHT.

423
00:27:40,893 --> 00:27:44,695
ONE. TWO. THREE.

424
00:27:44,764 --> 00:27:47,498
BROOTS!
OH, YEAH, OKAY.

425
00:27:59,245 --> 00:28:02,579
<i> [ Clattering ]</i>

426
00:28:04,617 --> 00:28:08,519
DAMN IT!
I'M SO TIRED OF BEING
LATE FOR THE PARTY.

427
00:28:08,588 --> 00:28:11,355
SHH. MISS PARKER,
WE MIGHT NOT BE LATE THIS TIME.

428
00:28:11,424 --> 00:28:14,725
LOOK AT ALL THIS STUFF.
TODAY'S PAPER.

429
00:28:14,794 --> 00:28:16,893
FOOD, CLOTHES, A D.S.A. PLAYER.

430
00:28:18,897 --> 00:28:21,031
THIS COMPUTER'S STILL WARM.

431
00:28:23,168 --> 00:28:25,169
JAROD'S STILL LIVING HERE.

432
00:28:25,238 --> 00:28:27,004
THIS IS TOO IMPORTANT
NOT TO TELL MR. LYLE.

433
00:28:27,073 --> 00:28:30,207
DON'T YOU THINK
THIS IS IMPORTANT ENOUGH
THAT WE HAVE TO LET HIM KNOW?

434
00:28:35,481 --> 00:28:39,383
SORRY. I-I GET HUNGRY
WHEN I'M NERVOUS.

435
00:28:43,156 --> 00:28:46,022
- PISTACHIO?
- BROOTS, WHEN EXACTLY...

436
00:28:46,091 --> 00:28:48,692
DID WE FIND THAT RECEIPT
IN THE BOX FROM JAROD'S LAIR?

437
00:28:50,529 --> 00:28:53,397
RIGHT AFTER MR. LYLE LEFT.

438
00:28:53,466 --> 00:28:55,398
WE'RE OUT OF HERE.
<i>WHAT?</i>

439
00:28:55,467 --> 00:28:58,803
WHY? WAIT. MISS PARKER?
WAIT, DON'T LEAVE ME HERE.

440
00:29:51,857 --> 00:29:54,258
<i>[ Melissa ]</i>
<i>I CAN'T BELIEVE THE DIFFERENCE.</i>

441
00:29:54,327 --> 00:29:59,230
I ALREADY FEEL
SO MUCH CLEARER.

442
00:29:59,298 --> 00:30:01,999
I SHOULD'VE KNOWN
SOMETHING WAS WRONG
WITH THOSE OTHER PILLS.

443
00:30:02,068 --> 00:30:04,335
HOW COULD YOU?
THEY BOTH LOOK EXACTLY ALIKE,

444
00:30:07,906 --> 00:30:12,642
MELISSA? I THINK IT'S TIME
THAT WE HAD A REAL TALK...

445
00:30:12,711 --> 00:30:16,312
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU.

446
00:30:16,381 --> 00:30:20,150
LOOK, YOU CAN PUT
LOCKS ON YOUR DOORS, YOU CAN
PUT BARS ON YOUR WINDOWS.

447
00:30:20,219 --> 00:30:22,952
BUT THEY CAN'T KEEP OUT
THE FEAR INSIDE OF YOU.

448
00:30:24,556 --> 00:30:27,456
YEAH, BUT I ALREADY TOLD YOU
EVERYTHING I COULD.

449
00:30:27,526 --> 00:30:30,226
THE REST JUST ISN'T THERE.

450
00:30:30,295 --> 00:30:33,462
THEN LET'S GO
FURTHER BACK...

451
00:30:33,531 --> 00:30:35,799
TO THE FIRST TIME
YOU WERE ATTACKED.

452
00:30:39,071 --> 00:30:44,473
- HOW DID YOU KNOW?
- CALL IT... A DOCTOR'S HUNCH.

453
00:30:46,945 --> 00:30:50,046
[ Chuckles ]
IT WAS BACK IN COLLEGE.

454
00:30:50,114 --> 00:30:53,215
YOU WENT TO MARRIETTA UNIVERSITY
WITH DR. ARNETT.

455
00:30:53,285 --> 00:30:55,217
YEAH.

456
00:30:56,755 --> 00:31:01,524
I WAS, UH, COMING HOME
LATE ONE NIGHT
AFTER STUDYING.

457
00:31:01,593 --> 00:31:03,593
<i> [ Sniffles ]</i>

458
00:31:05,263 --> 00:31:07,363
[ Sighs ]

459
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:12,268
I WAS, UH, PASSING BY
ONE OF THE OLD DORMS.

460
00:31:18,143 --> 00:31:22,746
A MAN IN A MASK
JUMPED OUT OF THE SHADOWS,

461
00:31:24,750 --> 00:31:27,116
GRABBED ME
AND PULLED ME INSIDE.

462
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:31,221
THEY NEVER EVEN CAUGHT HIM.

463
00:31:33,057 --> 00:31:35,091
BUT YOU BOUNCED BACK.

464
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:37,527
YEAH, I DID.
I REALLY DID.

465
00:31:37,595 --> 00:31:42,865
<i> I GOT COUNSELING,</i>
<i> I-I WORKED REALLY HARD</i>
<i> TO BECOME ME AGAIN.</i>

466
00:31:42,934 --> 00:31:45,534
<i> BUT ALWAYS</i>
<i> IN THE BACK OF MY MIND,</i>

467
00:31:45,603 --> 00:31:50,773
PART OF ME
IS JUST... SHATTERED.

468
00:31:52,544 --> 00:31:56,045
<i> I DON'T KNOW</i>
<i> IF I CAN BOUNCE BACK</i>
<i> THIS TIME.</i>

469
00:31:59,984 --> 00:32:03,152
NO. NO MORE CRUTCH.

470
00:32:03,221 --> 00:32:07,423
IT'S TIME TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED
DOWNTOWN THAT NIGHT.

471
00:32:07,492 --> 00:32:09,326
BUT HOW, JAROD?

472
00:32:09,394 --> 00:32:11,961
BY ASKING SOMEONE WHO KNOWS.

473
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:16,132
<i>LUKE, I WANT YOU</i>
<i>TO JUST IMAGINE</i>
<i>SOMEWHERE VERY PEACEFUL.</i>

474
00:32:16,201 --> 00:32:19,402
IT'S VERY SAFE.

475
00:32:19,471 --> 00:32:22,538
TELL ME WHAT YOU'RE SEEING.
TREES.

476
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:24,974
LOTS OF GREEN GRASS.

477
00:32:26,611 --> 00:32:31,146
THAT'S A-A PARK
I GO TO SOMETIMES,
NOT FAR FROM HERE.

478
00:32:32,284 --> 00:32:35,318
THERE'S A-A BENCH
I LIKE TO SIT ON.

479
00:32:35,387 --> 00:32:37,820
I LOOK UP AT THE CLOUDS.

480
00:32:37,889 --> 00:32:41,824
<i>ARE YOU HEARING ANYTHING?</i>
<i> MUSIC.</i>

481
00:32:41,893 --> 00:32:45,661
THERE'S A-A GUY
WHO'S ALWAYS THERE,

482
00:32:45,730 --> 00:32:47,663
AND HE BRINGS HIS CELLO.

483
00:32:49,101 --> 00:32:53,436
<i> [ Sighs ]</i>
<i> IT'S REALLY SOOTHING,</i>

484
00:32:53,505 --> 00:32:56,105
SITTING ON THE BENCH,

485
00:32:56,174 --> 00:32:59,676
JUST LISTENING
TO THE CELLO.

486
00:32:59,744 --> 00:33:02,812
<i>♪♪ [ Cello ]</i>

487
00:33:13,525 --> 00:33:16,559
YOU WERE RIGHT, LUKE.
IT IS RELAXING HERE.

488
00:33:16,628 --> 00:33:19,228
- WHAT THE HELL?
- YOU CAN RUN ALL YOU WANT.

489
00:33:19,297 --> 00:33:23,399
<i>BUT YOUR GUILTY CONSCIENCE WILL</i>
<i>BE TAPPING YOU ON THE SHOULDER</i>
<i>WHEREVER YOU GO.</i>

490
00:33:24,702 --> 00:33:27,803
LOOK, I TOLD YOU.
I'M NOT GUILTY OF NOTHIN'.

491
00:33:27,872 --> 00:33:30,173
I DIDN'T
ATTACK DR. BLASS.

492
00:33:30,242 --> 00:33:34,911
I KNOW.
BUT SOMEONE MADE YOU
LURE HER TO THAT HOTEL ROOM.

493
00:33:34,979 --> 00:33:38,080
WHY?

494
00:33:38,149 --> 00:33:40,383
<i> DR. ARNETT ATTACKED HER,</i>
<i> DIDN'T HE?</i>

495
00:33:42,453 --> 00:33:45,354
I DIDN'T WANNA CALL HER.

496
00:33:45,423 --> 00:33:47,657
I LIKE DR. BLASS.

497
00:33:47,726 --> 00:33:52,828
SHE WAS THE FIRST PERSON
WHO REALLY SEEMED
TO CARE ABOUT ME.

498
00:33:54,832 --> 00:33:59,001
BUT ONE NIGHT,
AFTER A SESSION,

499
00:33:59,070 --> 00:34:01,003
ARNETT GRABBED ME.

500
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:03,205
<i>HE TOLD ME</i>
<i>HE'D MAKE ME A DEAL.</i>

501
00:34:03,274 --> 00:34:05,775
HE SAID THAT
IF I GOT HER TO THE HOTEL,
HE WOULDN'T REPORT ME.

502
00:34:05,843 --> 00:34:07,777
I WAS, LIKE,
REPORT ME FOR WHAT?

503
00:34:07,845 --> 00:34:12,514
MISSED APPOINTMENTS.
PROBATION VIOLATIONS.
WHATEVER HE COULD MAKE UP.

504
00:34:12,583 --> 00:34:16,118
<i>HE SAID SENDING A DEVIANT</i>
<i>LIKE ME BACK TO PRISON WAS EASY.</i>

505
00:34:16,187 --> 00:34:19,021
<i>SO EITHER I CALLED</i>
<i>OR HE DID.</i>

506
00:34:21,292 --> 00:34:24,627
<i> THE NEXT DAY,</i>
<i> WHEN I HEARD,</i>

507
00:34:24,695 --> 00:34:29,398
I WAS, LIKE--
I FELT LIKE I WAS GONNA PUKE.

508
00:34:31,702 --> 00:34:35,605
DR. BLASS ALWAYS SAID,

509
00:34:35,674 --> 00:34:39,375
"RECOVERY IS A LONG ROAD."

510
00:34:39,444 --> 00:34:43,279
BUT ONE STEP AT A TIME...

511
00:34:43,348 --> 00:34:45,648
WILL GET YOU THERE.

512
00:34:45,717 --> 00:34:49,985
AND I WAS TAKING THOSE STEPS.
I WAS GETTING BETTER,
THANKS TO HER.

513
00:34:50,054 --> 00:34:53,089
WHY DIDN'T YOU
COME FORWARD?

514
00:34:53,157 --> 00:34:56,058
MY WORD VERSUS ARNETT'S?

515
00:34:56,127 --> 00:35:00,763
A LOWLIFE LIKE ME
AGAINST THE RESPECTED DOCTOR?

516
00:35:03,201 --> 00:35:05,134
NO ONE WILL EVER
LAY A FINGER ON HIM.

517
00:35:06,204 --> 00:35:08,270
DON'T BET ON IT.

518
00:35:18,916 --> 00:35:21,283
<i> JAROD.</i>
<i> YOU'RE WORKING LATE.</i>

519
00:35:21,353 --> 00:35:24,654
<i>YES. I HAVE A CASE THAT'S</i>
<i>STARTING TO TROUBLE ME.</i>

520
00:35:24,722 --> 00:35:27,256
ANYTHING I CAN HELP
YOU WITH?

521
00:35:27,324 --> 00:35:30,259
MAYBE YOU CAN.
BEING THAT YOU HAVE
SUCH AN INSIGHT...

522
00:35:30,328 --> 00:35:33,495
<i>INTO THE MIND</i>
<i>OF SEXUAL PREDATORS.</i>

523
00:35:33,564 --> 00:35:37,166
YOU SEE, I'M HAVING TROUBLE
UNDERSTANDING HIS MOTIVATION.

524
00:35:37,234 --> 00:35:40,402
<i> WELL, YOU KNOW, JAROD,</i>
<i> IT'S CONTROL.</i>

525
00:35:40,471 --> 00:35:43,672
SEX MAY BE
THE AVENUE THEY CHOOSE,

526
00:35:43,742 --> 00:35:48,177
BUT THE UNDERLYING MOTIVATION--
IT'S ALWAYS CONTROL.

527
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:53,215
<i> TO GET IT, HE PUTS</i>
<i> HIS VICTIM DOWN.</i>

528
00:35:53,284 --> 00:35:56,653
HE DEBASES THEIR HUMANITY.

529
00:35:56,721 --> 00:35:59,655
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
THE PREDATOR CAN CONVINCE
HIMSELF HE'S WORTHY.

530
00:35:59,724 --> 00:36:02,559
AND IF HE REFUSES
TO SEEK TREATMENT?

531
00:36:06,431 --> 00:36:08,964
WITHOUT ADMISSION
OF RESPONSIBILITY,

532
00:36:09,033 --> 00:36:10,967
THERE'S VERY LITTLE HOPE
FOR IMPROVEMENT.

533
00:36:11,035 --> 00:36:15,004
THEN I GUESS I'D BETTER FIND
A MORE RADICAL FORM OF THERAPY.

534
00:36:16,474 --> 00:36:19,375
THANK YOU FOR YOUR... INSIGHT.

535
00:36:42,067 --> 00:36:45,667
EVERYONE HAS FEARS.
TO THIS DAY, I'M HYDROPHOBIC.

536
00:36:53,478 --> 00:36:56,646
<i> SO, MONIQUE,</i>
<i> YOU WANNA PLAY DRESS-UP?</i>

537
00:36:56,715 --> 00:36:58,314
REALLY?

538
00:37:04,456 --> 00:37:06,388
<i> [ Door Closes ]</i>

539
00:37:07,692 --> 00:37:09,625
MELISSA?

540
00:37:11,062 --> 00:37:14,664
MELISSA, IS THAT YOU?

541
00:37:27,244 --> 00:37:30,679
MELISSA, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE OUT OF THE HOUSE
THESE DAYS.

542
00:37:37,889 --> 00:37:41,190
MONIQUE?
[ Groans ]

543
00:37:44,662 --> 00:37:47,896
JAROD.
JUST A B-12 SHOT,
DR. ARNETT.

544
00:37:50,235 --> 00:37:53,202
WHOOPS.
IT'S A SEDATIVE.

545
00:37:53,271 --> 00:37:58,407
DON'T YOU JUST HATE IT
WHEN MEDICATIONS GET SWITCHED?

546
00:38:08,553 --> 00:38:11,587
♪♪ [ Whistling ]

547
00:38:20,031 --> 00:38:23,098
[ Gasps ]

548
00:38:23,167 --> 00:38:25,100
JAROD?
<i> RELAX, DOCTOR.</i>

549
00:38:25,170 --> 00:38:27,570
<i> YOU'RE STRAPPED DOWN</i>
<i> AND GOING NOWHERE.</i>

550
00:38:27,639 --> 00:38:30,305
WELCOME TO THE EROS INN, DOC.

551
00:38:30,374 --> 00:38:33,208
OH, THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU'VE BEEN HERE BEFORE.

552
00:38:33,277 --> 00:38:35,645
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?

553
00:38:35,713 --> 00:38:41,283
JUST TRYIN' TO HELP YOU RELAX.
AND WHAT'S MORE RELAXING
THAN A NICE, WARM BATH.

554
00:38:41,352 --> 00:38:45,588
- NO, NO! NO, DON'T!
DON'T, DON'T, DON'T!
- THAT'S RIGHT. HYDROPHOBIA.

555
00:38:45,657 --> 00:38:48,924
<i> YOU REALLY SHOULD SEE</i>
<i> A THERAPIST ABOUT THAT.</i>

556
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:52,094
JAROD, YOU'RE CRAZY.
WHAT'D I EVER DO TO YOU?

557
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:55,731
OH, IT'S NOT WHAT
YOU DID TO ME. IT'S WHAT
YOU DID TO MELISSA BLASS.

558
00:38:55,799 --> 00:38:58,400
YOU'RE OUT OF YOUR MIND.
EVERYBODY KNOWS LUKE CARLO
ATTACKED HER.

559
00:38:58,469 --> 00:39:03,939
NOT EVERYONE.
ALLOW ME TO FLOAT MY THEORY.

560
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:06,175
[ Gasps ]
DAMN IT, JAROD!
YOU CAN'T DO THIS!

561
00:39:06,244 --> 00:39:08,277
IT'S ALL ABOUT CONTROL.

562
00:39:08,345 --> 00:39:11,680
<i> LIKE BACK WHEN YOU WERE</i>
<i> IN COLLEGE, WHEN YOU WERE</i>
<i> A MIGHTY BOBCAT.</i>

563
00:39:11,749 --> 00:39:14,516
<i>THE WAY YOU TOOK CONTROL</i>
<i>OVER THOSE FOUR INNOCENT GIRLS.</i>

564
00:39:14,585 --> 00:39:16,319
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKIN' ABOUT.

565
00:39:16,388 --> 00:39:18,821
I MAY NOT HAVE
ALL THE DETAILS, BUT I DO
HAVE THE BROAD STROKES.

566
00:39:18,890 --> 00:39:23,992
OH, SPEAKING OF STROKES?
DO YOU KNOW YOURS?
BREASTSTROKE. BACKSTROKE?

567
00:39:24,062 --> 00:39:26,928
'CAUSE YOU'RE GOING
TO NEED THEM THE WAY
THIS WATER LEVEL'S RISING.

568
00:39:26,997 --> 00:39:29,599
- I SWEAR!
- NOW YOU KNOW HOW MELISSA FELT.

569
00:39:29,667 --> 00:39:32,534
<i> POWERLESS. DROWNING</i>
<i> IN HER VERY WORST FEAR.</i>

570
00:39:32,603 --> 00:39:35,304
- WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?
- BECAUSE YOU DID IT TO HER!

571
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:37,673
JAROD, NO!
PLEASE DON'T!

572
00:39:39,877 --> 00:39:43,980
IT WAS HER FAULT!
I PUT HER DOWN 12 YEARS AGO!
SHE SHOULD'VE STAYED DOWN!

573
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:47,683
BUT SHE DIDN'T!
SHE WOULDN'T LET WHAT YOU
DID TO HER DESTROY HER!

574
00:39:47,752 --> 00:39:51,454
-SHE KEPT RUBBING IT IN MY FACE.
-THEN YOU TRIED TO RUIN HER
FOR GOOD.

575
00:39:51,522 --> 00:39:54,456
<i> FROM THE DAY YOU HIRED HER</i>
<i> AT THE CLINIC,</i>
<i> EVERY DAY SINCE THEN,</i>

576
00:39:54,525 --> 00:39:56,458
YOU'VE BEEN PLANNING
HER SECOND ASSAULT.

577
00:39:56,527 --> 00:39:58,327
SHE HAD TO LEARN HER LESSON!

578
00:39:58,396 --> 00:40:03,332
NOW IT'S TIME
THAT YOU LEARN YOURS.

579
00:40:07,939 --> 00:40:09,972
SHE HAD TO LEARN HER LESSON!

580
00:40:20,552 --> 00:40:25,587
[ Gasping ]

581
00:40:25,656 --> 00:40:28,090
<i> [ Water Off ]</i>

582
00:40:28,159 --> 00:40:31,460
LIKE YOU SAID, DOC,
EVERYONE HAS FEARS.

583
00:40:31,529 --> 00:40:34,197
[ Whimpering ]

584
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:50,746
MISS PARKER,
I WAS STARTING TO WORRY.

585
00:40:50,814 --> 00:40:53,616
I HADN'T HEARD ANY DEVELOPMENTS
IN YOUR JAROD PURSUIT.

586
00:40:53,684 --> 00:40:57,619
THAT'S BECAUSE
THERE WAS NO JAROD PURSUIT,
WAS THERE, LYLE?

587
00:40:57,688 --> 00:41:00,523
IT WAS ALL JUST A SETUP.
THE BOGUS SHIPPING REPORT,

588
00:41:00,592 --> 00:41:02,591
THE FAKE LAIR
WITH ALL THE SEX TOYS.

589
00:41:02,659 --> 00:41:05,528
THE SWINGING COUPLE, HOWEVER,
WAS A VERY CUTE TOUCH.

590
00:41:05,597 --> 00:41:09,498
<i>YOU DON'T USUALLY</i>
<i>SHOW SO MUCH IMAGINATION</i>
<i>WHEN TRYING TO SCREW ME OVER.</i>

591
00:41:09,566 --> 00:41:12,634
I DON'T HAVE
THE FOGGIEST IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

592
00:41:12,703 --> 00:41:18,407
NEXT TIME, DO YOUR HOMEWORK.
JAROD'S ALLERGIC TO PISTACHIOS.

593
00:41:27,385 --> 00:41:31,253
-<i> [ Broots ]</i>
<i> GOD, SHE'S AMAZING.</i>
- GO ON, TELL HER.

594
00:41:31,322 --> 00:41:35,424
<i>NO, SYD.</i>
<i>WOMEN DON'T WANNA BE TOLD.</i>
<i>THEY WANNA BE SHOWN.</i>

595
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:38,794
IT'S TIME I MAKE MY MOVE.

596
00:41:45,737 --> 00:41:49,605
BROOTS, I'M FLATTERED.

597
00:41:49,674 --> 00:41:52,241
IN FACT,
IT'S KIND OF SWEET.

598
00:41:54,145 --> 00:41:56,812
BUT IT'S NEVER GONNA HAPPEN.

599
00:41:59,017 --> 00:42:01,850
GOOD LUCK WITH
THE CHINNY-CHIN-CHIN.

600
00:42:28,445 --> 00:42:30,612
MMM.

601
00:42:32,483 --> 00:42:34,850
MMM.

602
00:42:34,919 --> 00:42:38,120
OH, THAT SUN FEELS NICE.

603
00:42:38,189 --> 00:42:41,891
[ Sighs ]
WELL, IT'S A START, HUH?

604
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:45,160
TODAY THE PORCH,
TOMORROW THE WORLD.

605
00:42:47,365 --> 00:42:49,665
MELISSA, THERE'S A LOT
OF PEOPLE WHO MISS YOU,

606
00:42:49,734 --> 00:42:54,169
WHO WANT--
WHO NEED YOUR HELP.

607
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:58,240
WELL, I'M SURE
HELPING THEM...

608
00:42:58,309 --> 00:43:00,909
WILL BE
THE BEST THERAPY FOR ME.

609
00:43:00,978 --> 00:43:04,113
ONE STEP AT A TIME
IS THE BEST THERAPY.

610
00:43:04,182 --> 00:43:07,482
JAROD, THANK YOU.

611
00:43:15,593 --> 00:43:18,226
GOOD LUCK.

